<item>
            <title>[AMQ-9716] maxMessageSize behavior changed for value -1 (since 5.19.0)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-9716</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In RESTful API the behavior of maxMessageSize with value -1 has changed/is buggy. As documented the message size limit should be disabled with this value. But since version 5.19.0 this behavior does not work anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug was introduced with commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/activemq/commit/8c12033261e097503851b30fbf6a8ce302e6f616&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;[AMQ-9519] Remove runtime usage of commons-io -  apache/activemq@8c12033 -  GitHub&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Little side note: Also with this commit a hard coded limit of Integer.MAX_VALUE was introduced, which is not documented. I guess that this limit is not really an issue for anyone - at least not for us.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A fix must be applied in two places:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/activemq/blob/main/activemq-web/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/web/MessageServletSupport.java#L362&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/activemq/blob/main/activemq-web/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/web/MessageServletSupport.java#L362&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/activemq/blob/main/activemq-web/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/web/MessageServletSupport.java#L403&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/activemq/blob/main/activemq-web/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/web/MessageServletSupport.java#L403&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
